Subject: [PATCH 12/12] feat: __chameleon API - trusted C++ click/query in
 isolated worlds

Add ChameleonBinding that injects __chameleon object into CDP isolated
world contexts. Provides:
- __chameleon.click(element) - DispatchSimulatedClick with kFromUserAgent,
  generates isTrusted:true events indistinguishable from real user clicks
- __chameleon.query(selector) - deep CSS query through closed shadow roots

Installed via local_window_proxy.cc on context creation. Only available
in isolated worlds when --chameleon-pierce is active. Page JS never sees it.

Successfully solves Cloudflare Turnstile via cross-process CDP:
Target.getTargets -> attachToTarget -> createIsolatedWorld -> __chameleon

Includes multi-bot parallel runner and updated README with complete
Turnstile solve example.

